<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14185">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Wood%20Carving.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5967">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5967 mb-requirement-id-5968">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to
        encounter while wood carving, and what you should do to anticipate, help
        prevent, mitigate, or lessen these hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6_4Bpltbnkg" target="_blank"
          >Top 7 Safety Secrets I Wish I'd Known Before My First Cut! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5967 mb-requirement-id-5969">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries that could occur while
        wood carving, including minor cuts and scratches and splinters. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/A0EmfREhgRw" target="_blank"
          >The Emergency First Aid Kit for Woodworkers Need! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5956">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5956 mb-requirement-id-5957">
        (a) Earn the Totin' Chip recognition. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/awards/awards-central/totin-chip/"
          target="_blank"
          >Totin' Chip (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5956 mb-requirement-id-5958">
        (b) Discuss with your counselor your understanding of the Safety
        Checklist for Carving. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Wood%20Carving/WoodcarvingChecklist.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Checklist for Carving (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5959">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5959 mb-requirement-id-5960">
        (a) Explain to your counselor, orally or in writing, the care and use of
        five types of tools that you may use in a carving project. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vMrwACL0Yrc" target="_blank"
          >Basic Hand Carving Tools Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5959 mb-requirement-id-5961">
        (b) Tell your counselor how to care for and use several types of
        sharpening devices, then demonstrate that you know how to use these
        devices. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/D6cy4av-18c" target="_blank"
          >Essential Sharpening Tools Every Wood Carver Needs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lBXRkMZfIXk" target="_blank"
          >How To Use a Sharpening Stone | Knives (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5Tt3K-kXhJc" target="_blank"
          >Fast and Easy Knife Stropping Guide (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5962">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Using a piece of scrap wood or a project on which you are working, show
      your counselor that you know how to do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5962 mb-requirement-id-5963">
        (a) Paring cut <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/V89HIK33dgQ" target="_blank"
          >Pairing Cut Safety Whittling With a Knife (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5962 mb-requirement-id-5964">
        (b) Basic cut and push cut <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ELvvu4wwMgM" target="_blank"
          >Push Cut Tutorial | Beginner's Wood Carving Guide (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5962 mb-requirement-id-5965">
        (c) V cut <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8NdNyjHm-fA" target="_blank"
          >V-Shaped Cut Technique |Essential Carving Technique | Whittling
          Basics (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5962 mb-requirement-id-5966">
        (d) Stop cut or score line <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/45xBl3kiShM" target="_blank"
          >How To Carve a Stop Cut | Woodcarving Fundamentals (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ckiBo5TLjk4" target="_blank"
          >Incise Woodcarving || The Basics of How to Incise Wood Carve "Line
          Carving" (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5970">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Tell why different woods are used for different projects. Explain why you
      chose the type of wood you did for your projects in requirements 6 and 7.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qnrBh3M1KQw" target="_blank"
        >Beginners Guide to Wood Carving - Lets Talk Wood (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/iIyU1Zx7tmI" target="_blank"
        >My Top 5 Favorite Carving Woods (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5971">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Plan your own or select a project from the <em>Wood Carving</em> merit
      badge pamphlet and complete a simple carving in the round. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/A1C40ObwTX0" target="_blank"
        >Making Your Own Carving Patterns—Whittling Tips for Beginners
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://caseknives.com/blogs/whittle-more/5-minute-wizard"
        target="_blank"
        >5-Minute Wizard (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7bQAa_CZsF4" target="_blank"
        >How To Whittle a Simple Bear—Step-by-Step Beginner Wood Carving Project
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/HimTJN3A3lw" target="_blank"
        >How To Carve a Arrowhead Neckerchief Slide Part 1 Carving Basics
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/CaP4V7CyYD8" target="_blank"
        >What Should You Whittle? Whittling Tips for Beginners (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5972">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Complete a simple low-relief OR a chip carving project. <i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/43dLqrKV9OI" target="_blank"
        >Beginning Woodcarving—How To Carve a Basic Flower With Mary May
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/spg4f_ge6Is" target="_blank"
        >Chip Carving w/ Wayne Barton —Introduction (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/bOE99r5N0Ds" target="_blank"
        >Chip Carving: Tips for Beginners (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
